# Git Workflow

## Commit Messages

```
<type>: <description>

<optional body explaining why>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `ci`

- Imperative mood, <72 chars subject line
- Body explains *why*, not *what* (the diff shows what)
- One logical change per commit

## Branch Names

`feature/short-description`, `fix/short-description`, `refactor/short-description`

## Pull Requests

- Analyze full commit history, not just the latest commit
- Use `git diff [base-branch]...HEAD` to see all changes
- Include a test plan with checklist
